Add a pure, tested location parser to `apps/desktop/src/components/recovery/recoveryFlow.ts`.

```ts
export interface JsonErrorLocation {
  line: number;
  column: number;
}

/**
 * Extract a 1-based line/column from a JSON parse error message. Handles
 * both serde_json's format ("... at line 12 column 5") — the shape of the
 * `error` string `get_state` returns for a corrupt state.json — and modern
 * V8's format ("Unexpected token ... (line 12 column 5)") that JSON.parse
 * produces, which `validateBackupShape` captures into a backup's
 * invalidReason. Returns null when no location can be found.
 */
export function parseJsonErrorLocation(message: string): JsonErrorLocation | null {
  const m = message.match(/line (\d+) column (\d+)/i);
  if (!m) return null;
  const line = Number(m[1]);
  const column = Number(m[2]);
  if (!Number.isFinite(line) || !Number.isFinite(column)) return null;
  return { line, column };
}
```

### Test — extend `__tests__/recoveryFlow.test.ts`
Add a `describe('parseJsonErrorLocation', ...)` block: (a) parses serde format `"expected value at line 12 column 5"`, (b) parses V8 format `"Unexpected token } in JSON at position 40 (line 3 column 8)"`, (c) returns null for a message with no location, (d) returns null for empty string.

### Scope
- Pure function only; no component or IPC changes in this phase.
- Case-insensitive match; tolerant of surrounding text on either side.

Use the Phase-1 helper in `apps/desktop/src/components/recovery/StateRecoveryDialog.tsx` (+ its CSS).

### Error summary callout
Import `parseJsonErrorLocation`. Compute `const errorLocation = useMemo(() => parseJsonErrorLocation(error), [error]);`. In the `recovery-error-summary` section, when `errorLocation` is non-null, render a structured callout between the label and the raw `<pre>`:
```tsx
{errorLocation && (
  <p className="recovery-error-location">
    Parse error at <strong>line {errorLocation.line}</strong>, column {errorLocation.column}
  </p>
)}
```
The raw `<pre className="recovery-error-message">{error}</pre>` stays — the callout surfaces the location, the pre keeps the full context.

### Preview state
Add `const [previewErrorLocation, setPreviewErrorLocation] = useState<JsonErrorLocation | null>(null);`. In `handlePreview(row)`, also set it: `setPreviewErrorLocation(row.valid ? null : parseJsonErrorLocation(row.invalidReason ?? ""));` — an invalid backup's `invalidReason` (from `validateBackupShape`'s captured `JSON.parse` message) yields the offending line. In `handleClosePreview`, clear it to null.

### Line-numbered preview with highlight + scroll
Replace `<pre className="recovery-preview-content">{previewContent}</pre>` with a line-numbered render: split `previewContent` on `\n`, map each to a row with a non-selectable gutter line number and the line text. The row whose 1-based index equals `previewErrorLocation?.line` gets an `is-error-line` class and a `ref` callback that calls `scrollIntoView({ block: 'center' })` once mounted.
```tsx
<div className="recovery-preview-content">
  {previewContent.split("\n").map((lineText, i) => {
    const lineNo = i + 1;
    const isErrorLine = previewErrorLocation?.line === lineNo;
    return (
      <div
        key={lineNo}
        className={`recovery-preview-line${isErrorLine ? " is-error-line" : ""}`}
        ref={isErrorLine ? (el) => el?.scrollIntoView({ block: "center" }) : undefined}
      >
        <span className="recovery-preview-gutter">{lineNo}</span>
        <span className="recovery-preview-text">{lineText || "\u00a0"}</span>
      </div>
    );
  })}
</div>
```

### CSS — StateRecoveryDialog.css
- `.recovery-error-location`: small callout, warning-tinted text, the `<strong>` slightly emphasized.
- `.recovery-preview-content`: keep it scrollable/monospve; switch from `<pre>` block styling to a flex/block column of lines (preserve the monospace font, border, max-height, overflow that the existing rule has).
- `.recovery-preview-line`: `display: flex`, monospace, `white-space: pre`.
- `.recovery-preview-gutter`: fixed-width (~3.5ch), right-aligned, dimmed, `user-select: none`.
- `.recovery-preview-line.is-error-line`: yellow/red-tinted background + a left accent border so the offending row stands out.

### Scope boundaries
- Frontend-only — no Rust/IPC changes. The corrupt state.json itself is not loaded into the dialog (no read-raw-file IPC exists and adding one is out of scope); the error-summary callout surfaces its location, which is what the user needs before clicking Edit Manually.
- The failing-row highlight applies to the **backup preview** for *invalid* backups (whose `invalidReason` carries a location). Valid backups preview with line numbers but no highlight — correct, they have no error line.
- No behavior change to list/restore/edit/reset flows.
